For some weeks ago, the Statistics page on Project is not working. 

Error Message pop-up says
{quote}The JIRA server could not be contacted. This may be a temporary glitch or the server may be down.{quote}

*Summary*
JIRA REST API for "search" no longer provide "transitions" expand field. JIRA throwing internal server error.
{noformat}
{"errorMessages":["Internal server error"],"errors":{}}
{noformat}

*Steps to reproduce*
# Login to JIRA Cloud
# Try to request the following REST:
#* https://<domain>.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/search?expand=transitions

Available expand field: {{"expand":"operations,versionedRepresentations,editmeta,changelog,renderedFields"}}

[At 18/11/2015 JIRA 7.0.2 was released|https://confluence.atlassian.com/jirasoftware/jira-software-7-0-x-release-notes-776997721.html#JIRASoftware7.0.xreleasenotes-v7.0.2-18November2015] with build number 70111. Currently the JIRA Cloud has version 7.0.0-OD-08-005 with the build number set to 70107. This causes following error while importing data to JIRA Cloud:
{noformat}
Storing import result with error type: DOWNGRADE_FROM_ONDEMAND
{noformat}

The problem will disappear with next JIRA Cloud release.

h2. Workaround

To workaround this issue build number stored in entities.xml should be changed from 70111 to 70107. The build number is stored in OSPropertyString with ID value referenced by {{entityId}} from {{OSPropertyEntry}} with {{propertyKey="jira.version.patched"}}.

{noformat}
<OSPropertyEntry id="1" entityName="jira.properties" entityId="1" propertyKey="jira.version.patched" type="5"/>
<OSPropertyString id="1" value="70107"/>
{noformat}

Also the {{UpgradeVersionHistory}} entry with {{targetbuild="70111"}} should be updated with {{targetbuild="70107"}} and {{targetversion="7.0.0-OD-08-005"}}

for example:
{noformat}
<UpgradeVersionHistory id="10100" timeperformed="2015-11-20 21:47:43.403" targetbuild="70107" targetversion="7.0.0-OD-08-005"/>
{noformat}

Look at these:

* {{%}}
* {{\%}}
* {{\\%}}
* {{\\\%}}

Now look at the source. That's how broken Jira's markup is. And it's much worse, with many more examples, but I like this one.

How would I get a backslash immediately followed by a percentage? Is it even possible? In and outside of a code 'tag'?

Affects EVERY version, not just 7.2.0, but that's mine.
